			<ns0:name>eaelt...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/103360015124260446450/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">At the moment we have a number of problems here:

- GDB interrupts by sending '0x03' single-char command. However, the stub now stops on any GDB data available;

- gdbserver handles GDB interrupt by sending SIGINT to the debuggee, thus GDB interrupt is a case of a signalled thread. At the moment we handle GDB interrupt differently, without using a signal, so in this case we do not have a signalled thread id. Investigate if this might confuse GDB...

